<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>NFA – Award Ceremony 2008 - Microsite</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by East Kent Housing</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Monty the Money Dog </span><br /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">multi channelled communication </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">approach to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">helps tenants </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in East Kent with their rent</span></p><p style="font-size:8pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:16pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold">Summary of case study</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">With the country facing some of the toughest economic times set against a background</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of the biggest welfare shake up the housing industry has seen for decades, it could be considered a small miracle for an organisation to bring down rent arrears and evictions for the second year running.  But that’s exactly what East Kent Housing has done</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> through the implementation of a new multi channelled communications approach which transformed the way they supported tenants to pay their rent.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">This new personalised approach included:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Changing how tenants were contacted to focus less on letters and more</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> on out of hour’s contact and the use of text. We send over 1,500 texts a month which has proved vital in engaging younger and harder to reach tenants</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A dedicated and cost effective communication campaign which used a mix of film, social media, literature and press to engage with over 17,500 tenants including teaming up with ‘Monty the money dog’ a fictional character that offers tenants advice on how to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> pay rent for the first time and general money advice </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">we are launching Monty’s own </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">facebook</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> page</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and twitter account</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> next week</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> which will provide regular money saving advice and budgeting tips</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">!</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Using ‘tenant made’ films to highlight the key points about </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the Governments Benefit Changes (</span><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c2ShlLL_j3A"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.youtube.com/wat</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">c</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">h?v=c2ShlLL_j3A</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">) and explaining how they can use a free online service to advertise their home to other tenants if they want to mutual ex</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">change (View here: </span><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E4_VPZvmrFs"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E4_VPZvmrFs</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.  These films were produced and made in house at no additional costs.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Through analysis of tenant arrears data, we identified the loc</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">al areas and tenant groups facing financial difficulty and targeted our approach.  E.g. Young single people living in tower blocks, many who have never lived alone before, were falling into arrears and were ignoring all contact.  A new tenant sign up proce</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ss was developed, which included setting up monthly payments and early intervention contact if the tenant fell into arrears.  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A new Benefits and Money Advisor team which provided tenants with personalised advice on maximising their income and budgeting ad</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">vice.  Since January 2013, over 500 people have been helped by the team with 150 tenants supported to downsize and/or receive extra income to help towards their rent</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Extending rent and money advice training to wider staff so they could discuss and provide </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">money and benefits advice through frontline services as well as make visits to those tenants not responding to letters or calls</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Introducing a more proactive and strategic direction to the way our rent team worked  which enabled staff to establish personal </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">relationships with their tenants which was pivotal to the team being able to understand the other ‘financial demands’ tenants are facing and plan the most effective approach to help them</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the successes?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The team have brought down tenant arrears for</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> two years running.  This is a reduction of £106,239 compared to when East Kent Housing took over rent collection when we launched in April 2011.  Evictions for rent arrears have fallen by 64%.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">multi-channel</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> communication campaign has been an overwhe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">lming success including 100% increase in website visitors in the last year (10,000 new visits).  Our ‘Tenant made’ Benefit Changes film has had over 1,200 views and over 80% of tenants affected by the benefit changes have been contacted and offered support</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Read more about our ‘Tenant made’ filming project here:</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="http://www.eastkenthousing.org.uk/about_east_kent_housing/communications_group/tenant_made_films.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.eastkenthousing.org.uk/about_east_kent_housing/communications_group/tenant_made_films.aspx</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">6 August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>